article_title: Israel’s Far Right Puts New Pressure on Netanyahu
article_text:
JERUSALEM—The violence emanating from Israel’s extreme right in recent days has prompted national soul searching and new questions about whether Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu’s government can hold.

An ultraorthodox assailant is accused of stabbing six people, one fatally, at Jerusalem’s gay-pride parade on Thursday, less than a month after he was released from prison on parole, having stabbed three people at the same parade in...
